al_main_2533329\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wfh1665702604181.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wfh1665702604181.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wfh1665702604181.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wfh1665702604181\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Validation and Modification Flags\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__validation_and_modification_flags_139211\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">All fields, keys, and occurrences have validation and modification flags which are used to determine data should be validated or stored. In general, when the content of a field is changed, the associated validation and modification flags are set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">TRUE</code>.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45110e1_d45111e1_d45112e1\">A field can be modified but not flagged for validation. This is the case when a field has been modified, successfully validated, but not stored.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45113e1_d45114e1_d45115e1\">You can also have new data with both validation and modification flags set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">FALSE</code>. This situation is common but not serious. It occurs when fields have been initialized by ProcScript or in field definitions.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__topic_d29242e1_d29243e1_d29244e1_d29245e1_d29246e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d587157e65\">\n                        \n Validation Flags\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45119e1_d45120e1_d45121e1\">Uniface checks the status of the validation flags to determine whether to activate the appropriate Validate triggers.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45122e1_d45123e1_d45124e1\">After successful validation the validation flags are set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">FALSE</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45125e1_d45126e1_d45127e1\">You cannot set the value of validation flags using ProcScript, but you can read them using the following ProcScript functions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22367e1_d22368e1_d22369e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdc1665702602510.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdc1665702602510.html\" title=\"Identify whether a field requires validation.\">$fieldvalidation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22370e1_d22371e1_d22372e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wcw1719485700746.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wcw1719485700746.html\" title=\"Identify whether a primary or candidate key requires validation.\">$keyvalidation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22373e1_d22374e1_d22375e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpz1719812992669.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpz1719812992669.html\" title=\"Check whether an occurrence requires validation.\">$occvalidation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22376e1_d22377e1_d22378e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"biz1719502191613.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/biz1719502191613.html\" title=\"Identify whether data in the component instance requires validation.\">$instancevalidation</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__topic_d29247e1_d29248e1_d29249e1_d29250e1_d29251e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d587157e126\">\n                        \n Modification Flags\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45131e1_d45132e1_d45133e1\">Uniface checks the status of modification tags to determine whether their associated Write triggers should be activated.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45134e1_d45135e1_d45136e1\">After the data is stored successfully, the modification flags are set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">FALSE</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__p_d45137e1_d45138e1_d45139e1\">You can read and set the value of modification flags using one of the following ProcScript functions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22379e1_d22380e1_d22381e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"swr1665702599962.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/swr1665702599962.html\" title=\"Return or set the requirement for field validation.\">$fieldcheck</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22382e1_d22383e1_d22384e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flp1665702599747.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flp1665702599747.html\" title=\"Indicate whether a specified primary or candidate key should be validated.\">$keycheck</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfh1665702604181__li_d22385e1_d22386e1_d22387e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hnz1719661363571.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hnz1719661363571.html\" title=\"Return or set the requirement for checking an occurrence.\">$occcheck</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533329\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533329\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Validation and Modification Flags Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Validation and Modification Flags All fields, keys, and occurrences have validation and modification flags which are used to determine data should be validated or stored. In general, when the content of a field is changed, the associated validation and modification flags are set to TRUE . A field can be modified but not flagged for validation. This is the case when a field has been modified, successfully validated, but not stored. You can also have new data with both validation and modification flags set to FALSE . This situation is common but not serious. It occurs when fields have been initialized by ProcScript or in field definitions. Validation Flags Uniface checks the status of the validation flags to determine whether to activate the appropriate Validate triggers. After successful validation the validation flags are set to FALSE . You cannot set the value of validation flags using ProcScript, but you can read them using the following ProcScript functions: $fieldvalidation $keyvalidation $occvalidation $instancevalidation Modification Flags Uniface checks the status of modification tags to determine whether their associated Write triggers should be activated. After the data is stored successfully, the modification flags are set to FALSE . You can read and set the value of modification flags using one of the following ProcScript functions: $fieldcheck $keycheck $occcheck Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}